headline: PayPal lifts 2025 profit forecast above estimates as turnaround picks up pace
summary: Under CEO Alex Chriss, PayPal has shifted its focus to profitability rather than chasing top-line growth.  PayPal's Venmo, a platform that has become virtually synonymous with peer-to-peer payments in the U.S., posted revenue growth of 20% for the second quarter.  On a per-share basis, the payments firm now expects an adjusted annual profit in the range of $5.15 to $5.30 versus its prior expectations of $4.95 to $5.10.
